page.title: 17STRUCTURE PLAN - WILLOUGHBY
page.content:
This policy seems to be working effectively as according to a local resident who has lived in Willoughby all his life, there have only been thirty seven houses built since the plan came into effect.
Although this may seem quite a number these houses are of an individual design and fit into the characterof the old village.
The number of houses built is in contrast to a neighbouring village, which was recently of a similar size but now contains three large, modern housing estates.
